title: Eyes on MSI: Uzi is King (2018 Mid-Season Invitational Finals)

json.text: Ming: Don’t rush. They lack items, they are trying to scale.  Caitlyn doesn’t have Shiv.
Uzi: It's fine, it's fine. Karsa: Unfortunate, unfortunate.
Uzi: This composition doesn’t have enough damage.
Uzi: It’s fine, it’s fine.
Uzi: It's fine, it's fine.
Karsa: It's fine, it's fine. Let's go, let's go!
All: AD AD AD!
Uzi: AHH! Kill him!
Xiaohu: Kill him!
Peanut: Kai'Sa died after flashing. This game is done. If we get inhib right now, this game's over.
Uzi: If we are really fighting, you guys need to frontline otherwise their damage is too high.
Uzi: I'll dive their backline.
Letme: Really?
Uzi: I have to dive their backline, otherwise we can't win the teamfight.
Uzi: They don't have QSS yet, it's up in 10 seconds.
Letme: Look mid, look mid! Xiaohu: Yeah, I think there's an opportunity.
Uzi: We can end! We can end! We can! We can! Nice!
All: We can! We can! Hit the turret!
Xiaohu: Nice, brothers!
To be honest, this has been my biggest dream for the past six years.
Achieving it today has made me so happy,
I never imagined that I would be standing here as the champion.
We are champions. Thank you everyone!
Interviewer: Holding that trophy now, are you really looking forward to returning to China, to Shanghai?
I'm really looking forward to it
because our organization has a lot of trophies, but no international ones yet.
When people come to visit our organization, this is a really powerful trophy for them to see.
